At least three people were killed and four others sustained various injuries in a collision in Bethal, Mpumalanga on Sunday.It is reported that two vehicles were involved in the head-on collision on the R35 in Bethal in the early hours of Sunday morning.Werner Vermaak from Arrive Alive said at approximately 3am they arrived on the scene where they found three people with fatal injuries.&#8220;There was nothing that could be done for them and they were declared dead on the scene and Two people were found with critical injuries and another two with moderate injuries,&#8221; said Vermaak.The exact cause of the collision is not yet known and Paramedics stabilised the injured on the scene before rushing them to a nearby hospital for treatment.TNA Reporter 